validateUser

public java.lang.String validateUser(java.lang.String username,
                                     java.lang.String password)
                              throws java.sql.SQLException
Validates a user against a database of usernames and passwords, returns "TRUE" followed by the user's data.

Does not throw a InvalidUsernameOrPasswordException, but rather returns "FALSE" in the event of a login error.

validateUser("testusername1", "password123") = "TRUE\nTest\nUser\n12";

Parameters:
username - a string of the username
password - a string of the password
Returns:
string a serialization of first name, lastName and number of indexed records separated by newlines
Throws:
java.sql.SQLException

getSampleImage

public java.lang.String getSampleImage(java.lang.String username,
                                       java.lang.String password,
                                       int projectId)
                                throws java.sql.SQLException,
                                       UserController.InvalidUsernameOrPasswordException
Gets the first image in a project to display as a sample.

getSampleImage("testusername1", "password123", 23) = "http://google.com/sample1.jpg\n";

In the event that the project does not exist, the username or password are incorrect or the project does not contain any images, getSampleImage will throw an exception

Parameters:
username - a string of the username
password - a string of the password
projectId - internal id of the project
Returns:
URL of the first image in the project
Throws:
java.sql.SQLException
UserController.InvalidUsernameOrPasswordException
